arch:property.oc:show_val: Small unit size with a fairly well preservation. It does not look very mixed. Most of the body parts are represented with most of the toes and vertebrae digested. High degree of bone processing can be attested by the presence of heavily fragmented toes. Mostly sheep/goat and also cattle-size animals are represented. Surface conditions of the bones are very good. There seems to be no attritional processes taken place witnessed by the presence of vulnerable elements such as unfused epiphyses of distal humerus, distal femur, and proximal tibia. Weathering stages 2 and 3 are mostly seen. Degree of burning is relatively low, not more than 10% in 4 mm sample, but 25% in the dry sieve. The unit suggests a small household activity or a small indoor midden due to its unmixed nature and well preservation. Nature of the breaks--sharp edges-- also confirms that there seems to be no transportation or secondary deposition. The unit looks like a primary deposit. 4 mm gave relatively large fragments. Last number = 120

arch:string.div: The unique identifier for each contextual unit, matching those used in the central Çatalhöyük excavation database and in publications. The excavation uses single-context recording.
